<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id122554d9-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s1106"><num value="1106">§ 1106.</num><heading> Inserting “compliments” forbidden</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A report, document, or publication distributed by or from an executive department or independent agency or establishment of the Government may not contain a notice that it is sent with “the compliments” of an officer of the Government, or with a special notice that it is so sent, except that notice that it has been sent, with a request for an acknowledgment of its receipt, may be given.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id122554da-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1261">82 Stat. 1261</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id122554db-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id122554dc-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 218 (<ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s73">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 73</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/620">28 Stat. 620</ref>).</p>
</note>
